        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Netanyahu to visit Hungary</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/israels-pm-netanyahu.png" alt="Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orbán invited Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu to Budapest in support and solidarity with Israel" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orbán invited Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu to Budapest in support and solidarity with Israel. Credits: Frumnews.com</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Israeli PM Benjamin Netanyahu <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-01-04-2025-h2-3-will-visit-hungary" target="_blank">will visit Hungary</a> this week despite an International Criminal Court (ICC) arrest warrant for alleged war crimes in Gaza. Hungarian PM Viktor Orban, a longtime ally of Netanyahu, has refused to enforce the warrant.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The visit comes as Netanyahu seeks international backing for President Trump’s controversial plan to reshape Gaza, which critics describe as ethnic cleansing. Hungary is technically obligated to follow ICC rulings but has remained silent. Israel has firmly rejected the charges, calling them politically motivated.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">This will be Netanyahu’s second foreign visit since the ICC issued warrants for him and former Defense Minister Yoav Gallant; the first visit being the US, which is not an ICC member. However, it is not the first time an ICC member has forgone making this type of arrest. Mongolia did not arrest Vladimir Putin when he visited in September 2024, despite being an ICC member.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
