        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Iran vows retaliation</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;"><strong>Summary: Iran's Khamenei vows retaliation if Trump's threat is enacted.</strong></p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Iran’s Supreme Leader, Ayatollah Ali Khamenei, <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-01-04-2025-h3-4-warns-of-a-strong-response" target="_blank">warns of a strong response</a> if President Trump follows through on threats to attack Iran over its nuclear program. Trump has reinstated his “maximum pressure” policy.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Trump recently sent Khamenei a letter urging nuclear negotiations and warning of military action if Tehran refused. Khamenei dismissed the likelihood of an attack but vowed a forceful counterstrike if provoked. Iranian FM spokesperson Esmail Baghaei condemned Trump’s remarks as a serious threat to international peace. In his first term, Trump withdrew the US from the 2015 nuclear deal in 2018 (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-01-04-2025-h3-5-white-house-statement" target="_blank">White House statement</a>).</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Iran has expanded uranium enrichment beyond the agreement’s limits while maintaining that its program is for civilian purposes. Iranian President Masoud Pezeshkian said Tehran would not directly talk with Washington. However, it will remain open to indirect negotiations.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Iran also adds that its nuclear program is strictly for civilian energy purposes.</p>
        </mj-text>
    </mj-section>
