        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">Who is the new PM of Greenland?</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/greenland-new-prime-minister-arctic-island-not-american.png" alt="Greenland’s new prime minister said the Arctic island won’t become American" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Greenland’s new prime minister said the Arctic island won’t become American. Credits: Leon Neal/AFP/Getty Images</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Jens-Frederik Nielsen, 33, has been sworn in as <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-01-04-2025-f1-6-greenlands-youngest-prime-minister" target="_blank">Greenland’s youngest prime minister</a>, riding his election promise of leading the semi-autonomous Danish territory toward independence through economic self-reliance. A former minister of industry and minerals, Nielsen faces growing external pressures, particularly from Trump’s ambitions to gain influence over Greenland’s mineral resources, including rare earth minerals.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">In his first address from Nuuk, Nielsen called for national unity and emphasized the need to move beyond reliance on Denmark’s nearly $1 billion annual grant and focus instead on business development and sustainable growth.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Nielsen’s leadership comes amid increased geopolitical tensions in the Arctic region. Despite Greenland’s rich deposits of minerals, oil, and gas, development has lagged, and US investment remains limited. Sworn in just hours before a US delegation arrived, Nielsen is also known for being a national-level badminton champion, hunter, and musician.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">He leads a coalition of parties from across the political spectrum, including his own pro-business, left-leaning Democrats. Colleagues describe him as charismatic, well-prepared, and socially intelligent. His leadership could mark a turning point for Greenland’s political and economic future as it navigates increasing international attention.</p>
        </mj-text>
